{{use dmy dates|date=August 2013}} {{Infobox royalty | name = Amr bin Mohammed Al Faisal | title = | image = | caption = | spouse = | issue = | full name = Amr bin Mohammed Al Faisal bin Abdulaziz Al Saud | styles = | succession = | reign = | reign-type = |reg-type = |regent = | predecessor = | father = [[Mohammed bin Faisal Al Saud|Mohammed bin Faisal bin Abdulaziz Al Saud]] | mother = Mona Azzam Pasha | birth_date = | birth_place = | house = [[House of Saud]] | almamater = | religion = [[Islam]] }}
'''Amr Al Faisal'''<ref>[https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/saud/interviews/amr.html Interviews: Amr Al Saud] ''PBS''</ref> ([[Arabic]]: عمرو الفيصل) is a Saudi businessman, columnist, architect and a member of [[House of Saud]].
==Biography== Prince Amr is the grandson of [[Faisal of Saudi Arabia|King Faisal]] who ruled the kingdom from 1964 to 1975. His mother is the daughter of [[Abdul Rahman Hassan Azzam|Azzam Pasha]], the first [[secretary-general]] of the [[Arab League]] between 1945 and 1952. He has two sisters.<ref>{{cite web|title=Family Tree of Mohammed bin Faisal bin Abdulaziz Al Saud|url=http://www.datarabia.com/royals/famtree.do?id=176260|publisher=Datarabia|accessdate=3 August 2013}}</ref>
Amr Al Faisal holds a bachelor's degree in architecture from [[King Abdulaziz University]].<ref name=itmaar/> He works in the field of commercial and investment banking, executive management, architecture and engineering. He is a member of the board of Faisal Islamic Bank in [[Sudan]] and [[Egypt]].<ref name=cpi>{{cite web|title=Ithmaar Bank B.S.C.|url=http://www.cpifinancial.net/directory/company/128/ithmaar-bank-b.s.c.-|work=CPI Financial|accessdate=3 August 2013}}</ref><ref name=itmaar>{{cite web|title=Board of Directors|url=http://ithmaarbank.com/ithmaar_glance_bod.asp|work=Ithmaar Bank|accessdate=3 August 2013}}</ref>
