[[Baron]] '''Rik Jaeken''' (born 1949, [[Bocholt, Belgium|Bocholt]]) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businessman who lives in [[Zonhoven]]. He was formerly president of [[UNIZO]] (1999-2007) and was succeeded in 2007 by [[Flor Joosen]].

Rik Jaeken is an engineer and president of a company active in selling and maintaining [[yacht]]s. He is vice-president of Trias, an organization which stimulates entrepreneurship in developing countries. In addition he is a [[Amateur radio operator|radio amateur]], nickname ''ON1BJI'', and a member of the ''Belgian Radio Amateur Society'' (UBA) section Noord-Oost Limburg (NOL, E: North-east Limburg).

