{{Infobox person |name = Terron Schaefer |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_name = |birth_date = |birth_place = [[Brazil]] |death_date = |death_place = |body_discovered = |death_cause = |resting_place = |resting_place_coordinates = |residence = |nationality = |ethnicity = |citizenship = |other_names = |known_for = |education = |alma_mater = |employer = |occupation = Executive Vice President/Chief Creative Officer at [[Saks Fifth Avenue]] |years_active = |home_town = |title = |salary = |networth = |height = |weight = |term = |predecessor = |successor = |opponents = |boards = |religion = |spouse = |partner = |children = |parents = |relations = |callsign = |signature = |website = |footnotes = }}
'''Terron Schaefer''' is the acting Executive Vice President and Chief Creative Officer for [[Saks Fifth Avenue]].<ref>Sebra, Matthew. "10 Essentials: Terron Schaefer." GQ.com. GQ, 23 May 2012. Web. 28 Apr. 2013. <https://www.gq.com/style/ten-essentials/201205/terron-schaefer-10-essentials-interview>.</ref> Before becoming a part of the Saks team, he was the Senior Vice President of marketing for [[Warner Bros.]] Worldwide.<ref>"Terron E. Schaefer Bio." NBC.com. NBC, n.d. Web. 28 Apr. 2013. <http://www.nbc.com/fashion-star/about/bio/cast/terron-e-schaefer/703583/>.</ref> Schaefer is a buyer representing Saks Fifth Avenue on [[NBC]]'s [[Fashion Star]], seasons [[Fashion Star (season 1)|1]] and [[Fashion Star (season 2)|2]].
