{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}} {{Infobox person |image = |image_size = 170px |name = Urs Felber |caption = |birth_date = {{birth date|1942|7|10|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Egerkingen]], [[Switzerland]] |death_date = {{death date and age|2010|4|26|1942|7|10|df=y}} |death_place = |other_names = |known_for = |occupation = [[Businessperson|Businessman]] and [[design]] [[Innovator|pioneer]] |salary = |networth = |spouse = |children = |nationality = Swiss }}
==Life and career==
Felber was born in 1942 in [[Egerkingen]], [[Switzerland]], a small town in the canton of [[Solothurn]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.contractdesign.com/contract/Design-Industry-Mour-1724.shtml |title=Archived copy |access-date=18 July 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708191720/http://www.contractdesign.com/contract/Design-Industry-Mour-1724.shtml |archive-date=8 July 2011 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref> His family ran a local carpentry workshop.
From 1962 to 1965, he studied mechanical engineering at the [[ETH Zurich|Swiss Federal Institute of Technology]] (ETH) in Zurich. In 1964, he replaced a fellow student in his field study at a small furniture manufacturer company, De Sede. In 1966, he became a system engineer at De Sede. He took a 50 percent stake in the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moebelkultur.de/index.php/news/11810 |title=Nachrichten und Informationen aus der Möbelbranche |publisher=moebelkultur.de |date= |accessdate=2013-06-13}}</ref> By 1978, De Sede was exporting to over 70 countries and reached a turnover of 85 million CHF.
In 1979, he obtained a PhD in Design Management at [[Stanford University]], [[California]] and the [[University of Fribourg]], [[Switzerland]], graduating ''[[magna cum laude]]''. He authored ''Systematic Design Management in the Enterprise: Fundamentals and Concepts'' which heralded the birth of [[design management]], design science and methodology.<ref>Urs Felber, "Systematisches Designmanagement in der Unternehmung: Grundlagen und Konzepte", Marburg, 1984</ref>
In the 1980s, he became a business partner and CEO of [[Vitra (furniture)|Vitra]] USA, the world's leading contract furniture manufacturing firm.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.contractdesign.com/contract/ls/article-archive.html?articletitle=COLUMNS-NONE_Focus_%20Ones%20to%20Watch_565.xml |title=Archived copy |access-date=18 July 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708191644/http://www.contractdesign.com/contract/ls/article-archive.html?articletitle=COLUMNS-NONE_Focus_%20Ones%20to%20Watch_565.xml |archive-date=8 July 2011 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Parallel to his US activities, he became a board director in several companies, such as [[Wilkhahn International]], [[Wilkhahn Switzerland]], [[Swissflex]] and [[Team by Wellis]].
In 2001, Urs Felber bought Swiss furniture company [[Dietiker AG]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metropolismag.com/story/20071104/dietiker-swizterland |title=Dietiker Switzerland |last1=Vlessing |first1=Robert |last2=Lasker |first2=David |date=2007-11-04 |website=metropolismag.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120402184957/http://www.metropolismag.com/story/20071104/dietiker-swizterland |archivedate=2012-04-02}}</ref> from the supermarket chain [[Migros]] and transformed it into a recognized brand by bringing contemporary designs, with products winning the [[Red dot design award|Red Dot Design Award]] and [[NeoCon#Trade Fairs|Neocon]] Innovation Award. Dietiker became a leader in Switzerland and Europe in the contract furniture market.
==Awards and honors== In 1999, urs felber was made a Honorary Fellow of the Tel Aviv Museum of Art. In 2002, he received Doctor Honoris Causa]] from the [[University of Tel Aviv]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.tau.ac.il/news/engnews.asp?month=5&year=2003 |title=Tel Aviv University Webflash - May 2003 |publisher=.tau.ac.il |date= |accessdate=2013-06-13}}</ref> On 20 May 2003, the Aviva and Urs Felber Jubilee Plaza was inaugurated at Tel Aviv University in recognition of his commitment to the university.<ref>http://www.tau.ac.il/public-affairs/TAU_Insider_Fall06.pdf</ref>
==Death== Urs Felber died on 26 April 2010.{{Citation needed|date=August 2017}}
